= causation =
====== short ======
Are there causal relationships between events/objects/processes and what
distinguishes them from mere regularities.

Russell claimed that <q>in advanced sciences such as gravitational astronomy,
the word 'cause' never occurs,</q>(([[local:zz.texts/russell1917-mysticismAndLogic.pdf|_On the Notion of Cause_]])) and that <q>the word "cause" is so
inextricably bound up with misleading associations as to make its complete
extrusion from the philosophical vocabulary desirable</q>. i.e. Our best
theories of the world do not contain any term that might be translated into
English as <q>cause</q>.

